name: Joni Ernst
text: I‚Äôm proud of our achievements, and I‚Äôm glad for the leadership of @POTUS and folks willing to work together to get our economy moving. There is more work yet to be done, and I look forward to seeing our economy continue to achieve new heights.

name: Joni Ernst
text: Simply put, when Washington gives power back to Main Street, American families win.

name: Joni Ernst
text: Furthermore, cutting red tape and scaling back burdensome regulations has led to a surge in small business optimism.

name: Joni Ernst
text: For example, a business in Dyersville, Iowa invested 75% of their tax savings last year into their employees, giving $800 bonuses to their 162 full time workers. One of their employees said she planned to put her bonus into her retirement fund, an investment in her future.

name: Joni Ernst
text: The #TaxCutsandJobsAct has allowed Iowa‚Äôs job creators to invest in their workers and grow their businesses.

name: Joni Ernst
text: Nowhere is the power of this job creation more evident than #Iowa, where the 2.4 percent unemployment rate is the lowest in the nation. There are 64,000 plus jobs open in Iowa right now! Over 1.6 million Iowans are employed ‚Äì the most in our state‚Äôs history.

name: Joni Ernst
text: The tight labor market has drawn workers off of the sidelines. Folks that have been unemployed or underemployed are finding work.

name: Joni Ernst
text: Just as important, this economic growth has put upward pressure on wages, with the average hourly pay increasing by 3.2 percent from last year. Lower-wage workers saw some of the biggest increases.

name: Joni Ernst
text: Last Friday‚Äôs January jobs report is a continued good news story, with 304,000 new jobs added last month.  It is also an example of how Republican pro-growth policies are getting people back to work.

name: Joni Ernst
text: I rise today to speak on the strength of the U.S. economy. As President Trump said in last night‚Äôs #SOTU, ‚Äúour economy is thriving like never before.‚Äù
